"] [PlyCount "22"] 1.e4 e5 2.Nf3 Nc6 3.Bc4 Nf6 4.O-O Be7 5.Nc3 Nxe4 6.Nxe4 d5 7.d4 dxc4 8.d5 Nd4 9.Nxd4 Qxd5 10.Nf3 Qxe4 11.Re1 Qc6 12.Nxe5 Qf6 13.Bd2 O-O 14.Bc3 Bc5 15.Re2 Qf5 16.Qd5 Bd6 17.Rae1 Be6 18.Qxb7 f6 19.Nc6 Bd5 20.Rd2 Bxg2 21.Rxd6 Bxc6 22.Rxc6 Qg4+ 1/2-1/2 With Chess:Pgn you will find a game by $game->date or $game->game. For our last example we will have $game->date : "????.??.??" $game->game : "1.e4 e5 2.Nf3 Nc6 3.Bc4 Nf6 4.Ng5 d5 5.exd5 Nxd5 6.Nxf7 Kxf7 7.Qf3+ Ke6 8.Nc3 Ne7 9.O-O c6 10.Re1 Bd7 11.d4 Kd6 12.Rxe5 Ng6 13.Nxd5 Nxe5 14.dxe5+ Kc5 15.Qa3+ Kxc4 16.Qd3+ Kc5 17.b4# 1-0" The module provide a good set of tools to modify PGN File but you will have to make yourself the while :)','files' => ['Makefile.PL','README','MANIFEST'],'lines' => {'nonpod' => 218,'pod' => 145,'total' => 363,'with_comments' => 1},'testers' => {'pass' => 7}},'ChildExit_0-1.tar.gz' => {'author' => 'TQISJIM','description' => 'alt Apache::Registry END block handler','files' => ['Makefile.PL','README','MANIFEST'],'lines' => {'nonpod' => 83,'pod' => 96,'total' => 179,'with_comments' => 8},'testers' => {'pass' => 3}},'Chipcard-CTAPI-0.1.tar.gz' => {'author' => 'WHOM','description' => 'Communication with chipcard terminals','files' => ['Makefile.PL','README','MANIFEST'],'lines' => {'nonpod' => 926,'pod' => 580,'total' => 1506,'with_comments' => 138}},'CircuitLayout-0.0.3.tar.gz' => {'author' => 'SCHUMACK','description' => undef,'files' => ['README','Build.PL','META.yml','MANIFEST'],'lines' => {'nonpod' => 2265,'pod' => 441,'total' => 2706,'with_comments' => 288}},'Cisco-Conf-0.10.tar.gz' => {'author' => 'JWIED','description' => 'Perl module for configuring Cisco routers via TFTP','files' => ['Makefile.PL','README','MANIFEST'],'lines' => {'nonpod' => 882,'pod' => 340,'total' => 1222,'with_comments' => 74},'testers' => {'pass' => 4}},'Cisco-CopyConfig-1.2.tgz' => {'author' => 'AARONSCA','description' => 'IOS running-config manipulation','files' => ['Makefile.PL','MANIFEST'],'lines' => {'